name: Walworth Gardens
directions: As you come in through the gate follow the path straight, on the left there's a building (with approach ramp). If you ring the bell staff will come out to greet you; ask them to use the toilets. It's the first right inside the building. Walworth gardens is open everyday (If the giant front gate is open it's open. closed: late evening &night). It's on the corner of braganza street opposite Pasley Park Walworth Garden, 206 Manor Pl, London SE17 3BN
comment: I'm disabled and genderfluid and worked there and it's a unisex toilet. Staff shouldn't be weird, they've been very positive with my disability, pronouns and queerness. Am openly out as trans the CEO is consistantly very polite. It's a greenspace charity that sells plants and holds workshops so they will probably try to sell you plants. The whole gardens is essentially a quiet space full of little hidey holes and it's usually not populated. it's free & encouraged to sit about so if you are neurodivergent it's a good place to hide in london or have mental health problems/ a bad day and want to get out of the house without the hustle& bustle. I'd probably go there more if the staff didn't know me professionally. that good goblin/cottagecore energ.
